          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Many in-source deprecation annotations—such as the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "@available",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " attribute in Swift—allow you to specify a plain text deprecation message.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You can use the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "@DeprecationSummary",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " directive to override that deprecation message with one or more paragraphs of formatted documentation markup.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "For example,",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "@DeprecationSummary {",
            "    This method is unsafe because it could potentially cause buffer overruns.",
            "    Use ``getBytes(_:length:)`` or ``getBytes(_:range:)`` instead.",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "md",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You can use the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "@DeprecationSummary",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " directive top-level in articles, documentation extension files, or documentation comments.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Before Swift-DocC 6.1, ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "@DeprecationSummary",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " was not supported in documentation comments.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Earlier versions",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "If you are writing a custom deprecation summary message for an API or documentation page that isn’t already deprecated,",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "you should also deprecate it—using in-source annotations when possible or ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/Available",
                  "isActive" : true,
                  "type" : "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " directives when in-source annotations aren’t available—so that the reader knows the version when you deprecated that API or documentation page.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
